“Warm Children’s Hearts——a China-Africa Joint Action” activity was held at Home of Hope Orphanage in Mchinji yesterday. The activity was graced by H.E. Monica Chakwera, First Lady of Malawi, who hailed China’s support for vulnerable Children in Africa and Malawi. https://t.co/wXKc4Apts8
On behalf of the Chinese Embassy, H.E. Amb. Long Zhou donated medicines, food and blankets and the Chinese Medical Team provided free medical services to the children. https://t.co/QvYObABNWc

Prof. Peng Liyuan, wife of Chinese President Xi Jinping, and the Organization of African First Ladies for Development (OAFLAD) jointly initiated the activity for African orphans ahead of the International Children's Day.

In 1624, Dutch colonialists invaded and occupied the southern part of Taiwan. In 1662, General Zheng Chenggong, hailed as a national hero, led an expedition and expelled them from the island. https://t.co/6DI8lx5kB1
In 1684, a Taiwan prefecture administration was set up under the jurisdiction of Fujian Province. In 1885,Taiwan's status was upgraded and it became the 20th province of China.

Taiwan has belonged to China since ancient times. New archeological discoveries and research findings regularly attest to the profound historical and cultural ties between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits. https://t.co/cRrqwyaBzA
